{"title":"Podcast #079 – Triton Bikes’ Amazing Escape From Russia","link":"https://bikerumor.com/podcast-079-triton-cycles-amazing-escape-from-russia/","date":1680287908000,"content":"<p>I think, at some level, we all crave adventure. It’s why the “zombie apocalypse” genre is so popular. What would we do if we had to drop everything and just … escape? Start fresh.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, for many folks around the world, it’s not a fantasy. It’s why we have so many people trying to migrate into the USA and most of Europe. They’re trying to escape a desperate if not downright dangerous situation.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And that’s where we pick up in this episode, bringing it close to home with my friend Dmitry Nechaev (pronounced <em>neeh-chive</em>). He’s the founder of <a href=\"https://triton-bikes.com/en/triton-groont-en/\" target=\"_blank\">Triton Bikes</a>, which, up until very recently, was based in Russia and making gorgeous custom titanium bicycles.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Everything changed for him when Russia invaded Ukraine, and his story about how he and his family got out, and how he eventually relocated the business, his employees, and equipment to Portugal is <em>WILD!</em></p>\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n<p>From sneaking parts out to having friends and co-workers ride for days to cross by bicycle at remote border stations, he has some stories to tell. We talk about why he’s living in Israel but relaunching in Portugal, and, toward the end, we talk about how they’re rebuilding the brand getting ready to build its first bikes in its new factory.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-nahbs-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"649\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-nahbs-bike-800x649.jpg\" alt=\"Triton cycles van with NAHBS road bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-nahbs-bike-800x649.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-nahbs-bike-297x241.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-nahbs-bike-120x97.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-nahbs-bike-768x623.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-nahbs-bike-1536x1247.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-nahbs-bike.jpg 1800w\" /></a><figcaption>Dmitry with his road bike and new delivery van.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s a long one, but stay tuned at the end for a recap of a few other things we discussed after I stopped recording. Scroll below for some photos from his journey and setting up the new factory.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-8.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"1067\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-8-800x1067.jpg\" alt=\"Triton cycles driving out of russia\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-8-800x1067.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-8-225x300.jpg 225w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-8-90x120.jpg 90w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-8-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-8-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-8.jpg 1400w\" /></a><figcaption>Driving out of Russia.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"1067\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-7-800x1067.jpg\" alt=\"Dmitry's Land Rover\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-7-800x1067.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-7-225x300.jpg 225w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-7-90x120.jpg 90w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-7-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-7-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-7-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-7.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>Dmitry’s Land Rover, which a friend drove out of Russia for him, with his bike inside.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"1067\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-6-800x1067.jpg\" alt=\"Land Rover in front of the Eiffel Tower\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-6-800x1067.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-6-225x300.jpg 225w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-6-90x120.jpg 90w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-6-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-6-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-6.jpg 1400w\" /></a><figcaption>Sights along the way from picking up his truck north of Russia, heading to Portugal.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"897\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-5-800x897.jpg\" alt=\"Welcome to Portugal sign\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-5-800x897.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-5-268x300.jpg 268w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-5-107x120.jpg 107w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-5-768x861.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-5-1371x1536.jpg 1371w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-5.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-4-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"The new Triton HQ and factory in Portugal.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-4-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-4-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-4-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-4-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-4-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-4.jpg 1800w\" /></a><figcaption>The new Triton HQ and factory in Portugal.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"700\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-2-800x700.jpg\" alt=\"Loading new machines in the new Portugal HQ\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-2-800x700.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-2-297x260.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-2-120x105.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-2-768x672.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-2.jpg 1462w\" /></a><figcaption>Loading in the new machines.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-1-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"Inside the new factory and HQ in Portugal\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-1-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-1-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-1-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-1.jpg 1800w\" /></a><figcaption>The beginnings of a new Triton production line.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"350\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-3-800x350.jpg\" alt=\"Some of Triton's fixtures they were able to get out of Russia\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-3-800x350.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-3-297x130.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-3-120x52.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-3-768x336.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-3-1536x672.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-escape-to-portugal-3-2048x896.jpg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>Some of Triton’s fixtures they were able to get out of Russia.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-groont-gravel-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"521\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-groont-gravel-bike-800x521.jpg\" alt=\"Triton Groont titanium gravel bike, shot before the exodus\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-groont-gravel-bike-800x521.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-groont-gravel-bike-297x193.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-groont-gravel-bike-120x78.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-groont-gravel-bike-768x500.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/triton-cycles-groont-gravel-bike.jpg 1440w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A huge thanks to Dmitry for sharing his story with us. And if you’re looking for a new bike, please check out Triton and point some friends its way — it’ll help Triton rebuild the business. Visit its website, <a href=\"https://triton-bikes.com/en/triton-groont-en/\" target=\"_blank\">Triton-Bikes.com</a>. And Follow Triton on <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/tritonbikes/\" target=\"_blank\">Instagram</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tritonbikes/\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a> too!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Want More?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Find the BikeRumor Podcast on <a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/bikerumor-podcast/id1455519558\" target=\"_blank\">Apple Podcasts</a>, <a href=\"https://www.stitcher.com/podcast/bikerumor-podcast\" target=\"_blank\">Stitcher</a>, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.podbean.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Podbean</a>, and through <a href=\"https://feed.podbean.com/bikerumor/feed.xml\" target=\"_blank\">RSS</a>, or wherever you listen to podcasts! Hit like, hit subscribe, and hit play! Can’t find it? Let us know which players you use so we can get them up to speed! And let us know who you want us to interview, just <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/podcast/\">use this form</a> to send us your suggestions!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>FOLLOW BIKERUMOR</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Keep tabs on all the latest bikes, wheels, components, gear, and tech on The World’s Largest Cycling Tech Blog by following us on <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/bikerumor\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a>, <a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/bikerumor\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter</a>, and <a href=\"http://www.instagram.com/bikerumor\" target=\"_blank\">Instagram</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>FOLLOW TYLER</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Like us? Love us? Follow your host, Tyler Benedict, on <a href=\"https://www.twitter.com/tylerbenedict\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/tylerbenedict\" target=\"_blank\">Instagram</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/tylerbenedict\" target=\"_blank\">LinkedIn</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/